  "text": "We now return to a version of the OFC model with finite earthquake duration, which means that we skip the separation of time scales between individual events and long-term driving. In the context of basic SOC models, the first systematic study in this direction was published by [CITATION_1] . This study referred to a one-dimensional sandpile model, the \"Oslo\" model. It was found that, depending on the duration of individual events, avalanche merging occurs which finally turns into continuous flow. A version of the OFC model with finite event duration was considered by [CITATION_2] in the context of solar flare statistics.",
